content: Horrible For your money you get 100 puzzles. That's it. I expected some decent tutorials, perhaps a tool I could use to enter puzzles from a newspaper so I could work on them. Nope. Nothing at all. Worse still is the fact that some of the so-called hints are quite wrong -- or incomplete. #36 for example

500 characters isn't enough so i'll write in short form Cracking the Cryptic is awesome/ Mark and Simon are awesome/ the hand crafted and tested puzzles are awesome/ this app is not good... at all. if a bare-bones, barely functional app is your thing then you'll like this one if you were expecting a top-notch app worthy of the name 'Cracking the Cryptic' then you'll be as disappointed as i am right now. Something, something, something... disappointing! Did i mention: Disappointing!
Great variety of different styles and difficulty of boards. Truly excellent .
Great game, interface is the best I've seen for sudoku. Puzzle selection is great, I'm going to be bummed when I finish them all.

I loved this app...until it stopped working. I have a Pixel 4a and just recently I haven't been able to get past the start screen. It's really sad because it's a great app, but it's currently unplayable for me.
Straight forward and simple design. Controls make sense and are easy to use for different types on annotations. Hints are useful and don't give too much away.

This is a great app for advanced sudoku players who want to use the same notation as Cracking the Cryptic on YouTube. I haven't found any other apps that let you use this notation. I highly recommend trying it out on their website first (there's an online demo that works on mobile as well as desktop), but once I gave it a shot, I was hooked and couldn't ever go back to other apps, even if this one isn't particularly pretty.
Best suduko ui
Love this app! The puzzles are interesting And the difficulty progression is really manageable
Fantastic app with amazing puzzles. Cracking the cryptic produce the best handmade boards out there. I have 4 of the 6 apps at the moment and plan on gettibg the others 2 after Christmas.

Great app with accurately selected problems and Some useful tools I didn't found in other apps. Awesome the idea of adding hints. The gameplay is rather tricky. What a shame there is no the custom sudoku option, maybe in some update...
Great game crafted puzzles with fun logic as you increase in difficulty. Hints are very often wrong though, wish they had proof read them.
Best Sudoku app I've used, out of many.

It's good fun but has room to grow. The UI is a bit cumbersome. Also, don't take the difficulty stars seriously. I did a 10-star in 20 minutes but a 5-star took me an hour. It's all about your strengths and weaknesses.
Great app for doing sudoku. Fantastic interface. Really good way to learn new techniques.

Great app with fun challenging puzzles. The first app I've spent money on and pretty happy except the hints feature. Not what i was expecting. Nothing to do with logic, just "Hey there's a 5/7 pair in r7c8c9" or something like that. Some of them are completely wrong too. Puzzle #41, Hint #1 says there is a 1 in r8c9 but r8c9 is a given 2. Good puzzles and good tools but kinda jank here and there.
Previously given 5 stars, however the updates has been non existent for the past month? Me need Sudoku.
Najlepsza aplikacja sudoku!
Great app, beautiful puzzles. The hints really helped me hone my solving skills :)

Really good difficult puzzles some take 5-10 minutes, others take me over an hour. The interface is great though i wouldn't say no to a better sideways mode. Having multiple mark types really helps me get through some difficult points.

I hate paying for apps but this one is genuinely worth the price. The functionality of this app is perfect. It took me a few attempts to get the settings just right for my liking, but once I did it became a dream to use. And it seems you can change just about every bit of it, so you're sure to find a setting that works for you. I've only gone through a handful of the puzzles so far, but they seem far better than the computer generated ones you see on the free apps.
Corner notation puts the 5 in the middle instead of the corner. Can't distinguish the given numbers from my entered numbers.

I'm not sure if I'm doing something wrong. I downloaded this app to increase my logic understanding for harder puzzles. But most of them are locked even after paying for the app? I can see that down the track with very difficult puzzles I won't be able to complete them to get stars to unlock. I can also only see two hints (it says locked?). The two hints also don't correlate to where I am up to with the puzzle (unless there is a way to unlock all hints for a puzzle???) PLEASE HELP!
Need more puzzles I am hooked on these

Great app, easy to use. Love that the puzzles are hand made and logic based. Some feedback: - it would be good if the puzzle had a link to a YouTube cracking the cryptic solve if there is one! - Id prefer the hints to give clues on particular logic to lookout for e.g. look for an x-wing - Some bugs when filling in whole numbers, I'll select a number but it puts it in as a note instead of an actual. - settings are confusing, I don't understand what a couple of them mean (what are the Xs for...?)
Great app, fun puzzles, definitely worth the price
It's the little things like the new puzzle select menu that makes me love this app so much.
An excellent series of puzzles from superb setters. Even if you're not a whiz at sudoku, the functionality of the app will floor you. Simply, the best I've had the pleasure of using.
A very competent sudoku app, with hand-crafted puzzled. My only gripe is that after owning it for three months, I've only received one "monthly" update.

Great app but expensive. Also they promise 5 new puzzles a month. We're almost 2 weeks into August. Cmon guys. This is a premium product. We spent money to realize that, devs needs to treat it as a premium buy as well. I'm updating from 2 to 3 stars. After expressing frustration over the advertised "5 new puzzles a months" and getting nowhere asking in the CtC discord other than smarmy responses from fans and protectors of their brand, I emailed the developer and received my refund within hours
I'm getting much better at Sudoku by using this app and watching Cracking the Cryptic videos. Thanks Mark and Simon!!!
This are nice puzzles, now i understand what they mea with "this is absolutely beautiful this handmade sudokus really are. Only the hits, are not always clear...
A fantastic sudoku solving interface (annotations, colours), and a collection of challenging puzzles to solve. Perfect.
Have completed all the puzzles. Hope to have more soon...
They promised 5 new puzzles a month. They missed July but they finally released 10 new puzzles in August. Better late than never.

The app feels very unpolished. In several places, the content is not centered. The sync game progress feature does not sync the times. It absolutely destroys the battery life. I'm sure there is more that I'm missing.
Handmade puzzles much more interesting.
It's a shame this is a really good app but it just murdered my battery so fast I could never use it
Great as far as it goes. A shame these guys couldn't turn their forensic minds to the proof reading of the hints, which are so riddled with errors as often to leave one hanging mid puzzle.
Really love this app aside from the CRAZY battery drain. It's just a sudoku app but this thing uses up the most battery life out of any app I have.
THE best app for sudoku! I've tried many others and none of them compare. I think I hear Simon and Mark's voices in my head as I play but I'm sure that means I'm a devoted fan and not crazy.

Sadly I just couldn't adapt to the format. I'm used to and like the format which links from CTC you tube videos but found this unusable because you can't use centre pencil marks for square only candidates and corner marks for Snyder notation of only 2 possible in the box. Shame.

This is by far the best Sudoku app I have ever had. If you enjoy a beautiful solve and interesting logic chains look no further - those handcrafted puzzles are so much better, than the randomly generated stuff you get from free sudoku apps. At least for me the price is well worth the many hours of fun I've already had! I can also recommend the creators' youtube channel - those guys are brilliant!
Excited for the new puzzles

I absolutely love the controls and the ability to take notes in the cells in a variety of ways. I do not like the hints. Sudoku by Brainium has the best teaching hints around. Also, five new puzzles per month are not happening, which is part of the reason I purchased this app.

Premium price should mean premium app. There are shortcomings some of which really ought to be addressed considering the price. Monthly new puzzles are late.... .Well over a month since the last update. It does not show you which puzzles you are working on VERY ANNOYING. Hint text needs checking, spelling mistakes and procedural errors. Never mind Craking the Cryptic... Sort the app out to justify the price.
Hasn't had new puzzles for 7 weeks
I am out of puzzles and still sitting on the toilet. I need more.
Great Sudoku app. Increasing difficulty with decent hints
So got damn hard
Good overall but where is this months update? I burned through the previous months puzzle in a day. I need my fix... hahaha.

As a Sudoku app, it doesn't get better than this. The double notation, the amount of accessibility options and features is great. Moreover, the puzzles are amazing, and handcrafted with great hints that help you further develop your solving skills, going harder and harder in difficulty in a fair pace. However, there are some caveats, the UI sometimes it's a bit clunky, the menus and settings are not very tidy and the hints sometimes assume things that are not clear or they're all the way wrong.
Great puzzles and controls. I would love to see a custom puzzle option so we can input our own puzzles, it's fun following along on the channel sometimes.
Love the app, love the YouTube Channel. Keep it up. üòç
By far my favorite sodoku app. I appreciate the hand selected quality puzzles, however I wish you would give the option to import puzzles or auto generate them as well
bugs, no response...
Won't download

I use this app a lot, the puzzles are brilliantly curated. I love the dual markup system. However it is a massive battery drain, my phone goes from 100% it 0% in under an hour when I use this (on dark mode as dim as possible). Also it doesn't remember which puzzle you were last on which is very annoying.
Excellent design and easy to use. Not to mention some pretty mindbending sudokus.

Eh, it's alright. I refunded it as the hint was just 'you can put a number in a this cell', but doesnt tell you why. It's literally just giving you a number from the solution that would otherwise be unknowable. I was kinda expecting a more nuance clue than just an answer bank peek.
The hints are not straight forward. They are hard to follow and have no explanation. And some puzzles don't have enough.

It's been extremely enjoyable and educational. There is one thing that does irritate me a little. When I ask for a hint, the hint window covers the puzzle, so I have to cycle through the hint several times to see what the hint is saying. If I were able to move the hint aside to see the screen or maybe even have the hint window smaller can really help.
A sudoku games that teaches how to solve soduko from easy to very hard

The app worked good for 2 weeks, now it shuts own every few seconds.I re-open the app, play for a few seconds, or maybe even a few minutes, then bop! Shuts down. I ha another sudoku app - a free one and it never shut down, but the ads were horrible so I tried this one.

Love this app; it has the nicest UI I've come across in Sudoku games, and offers both pencil marks and pen marks, and cell colour coding with 3 different colours to help solve more advanced puzzles. My only improvement would be to add Google Play Games functionality so that your progress can be synced across multiple devices, as I definitely enjoy playing on a larger screen on the sofa!
After several weeks and getting 2/3rds of the way through the puzzles it's suddenly lost ALL of my progress and has reset back to zero stars and only puzzle 1 unlocked! Aarrggh!
Amazing! Huge fan of cracking the cryptic! The app does not disappoint! Worth the money.

Best engine I've seen in any sudoku game, mobile or otherwise. The puzzles are super hard. The two-star puzzles are already too much, and I can't understand the hints most of the time. For experts and advanced players, this is the best sudoku you will find on Android. This unity game is pretry resource intensive and unoptimized. It runs great, but expect older devices to heat up quite a bit. The creators have an excellent YouTube channel worth checking out. Please add more 1 star puzzles!
Loving it, great challenging puzzles. Controls are finicky and take a few games to adjust to. The hints are helpful and definitely develop my skills

Love the pencil marks. Much better than the other suduku game I play. Deducted 1 star from my review because it doesn't allow me to manually enter puzzles. For the price, I expect to be able to sit down and enter a puzzle myself that I want to play - ESPECIALLY since their YouTube channel will frequently show them playing puzzles from the newspaper.

The puzzles are great. The app, however, has some really annoying shortcomings. The top of the list is: The screen deactivates quite quickly when you don't interact with the app (because you might be thinking about the puzzle. Then, it's hard to find started games if the app was closed for some reason. Also, it would be really helpful if we could see the rating on the puzzle overview page as well.

This (and the PC version on Steam) is a Unity Game. Expect your phone to get red-hot after just 2 minutes of staring at a completely static grid of digits, for absolutely no reason. And that it sucks up your battery goes without saying. It's a shame. This app is probably has better pencil-mark options than most you'll see‚Äîbut still not as good as Cracking The Cryptic's own webapp. That is forgivable at least for this mobile version, but why-oh-why did you make it a Unity Game? Unhappy.
Great app

Wow, such a treat! So rarely there are challenging sudokus in apps, but this selection made me pause from time to time. You can see all the effort put in it, it's a pure joy to solve. The only problem - it gets over too soon!
The landscape format for tablets is wretched, it really ruined the experience for me. I have not played a game since the update. Please revert back to the portrait game format.

I'm not sure I've ever made a comment on any app before, but it must be said that this app is exceptional for anyone who wishes to improve their knowledge of sudoku as the hints really explain what to look for. I often revisit the hints just to see different examples of the various logical figures found in sudoku.
An excellent app - hints are useful while not breaking the puzzle completely, and the interface is simple enough once you get used to it.
Love the app, love the YT channel!

An awesome Sudoku app, really loved the note system and the ability to use 2 types of pencil marks. So far (up to #20) the puzzles have been challenging but also logical with no guess and check required.
Great way to learn sudoku, and some really excellent puzzles!
Great construction. Very challenging and enjoyable.
The best sudoku game I've come across. The care used in selecting quality puzzles is clear. More than worth the money. I'm looking forward to the other apps they offer.

The only app that lets you put notes in the middle AND outside. Only wish there was more puzzles, but I really like that the ones this has are all hand made. Makes it much more interesting to solve The fine tuning of settings is also a great plus. Lots of options to make it work exactly how I want
Handpicked puzzles, instead of generated ones, are much more enjoyable to play.
Great app. Controls are really good. If there could be a night mode, that would be excellent!
Great sudoku app. Wonderful YouTube channel.
Very good app. But it would be perfect if I could put my own board and solve them. Also sync would be good to have. Cause now I solve every puzzle twice. Thanks!

It's a very good sudoku app, the hand made puzzles are most interesting, and the hints teach you advanced moves. Coming from the YouTube channel I was a bit disappointed, although it's obvious in hindsight, that these are only classic sudoku puzzles, not the interesting variants from the YouTube videos. Still, love it. It spoils you for other sudoku apps which generate their puzzles using simple algorithms.

This app makes playing a joy! The ability to color squares and use center positions are a revelation. Some of the puzzles are truly challenging (and some are beyond my current level). They are much different than the computer-generated ones in other apps. I didn't realize there were hints initially, which is possibly my only complaint, but they're great! Having them done by a human is amazing. Even if you have no idea who Simon and Mark are (and they are awe-inspiring), this is worth getting. 5‚òÜ
5 stars for the channel, 4 for the application. Need more highlight colors for the Highlighter.
Would be 5* if we could create puzzles, then we can add the puzzles from your YouTube channel!
Best sudoku app by far! Keep up the good work!

Not fun. Easy way to hack the system...do not read the rest if you don't want to hear the hack.................. ..........................................................................................if you put in the wrong number it will show up red even if you haven't filled in the reason for it not to work.
The puzzles are great, but please roll all the apps into one! I don't mind paying for each type, but I'd so much rather have each puzzle pack be an in app purchase from a single app
Fantastic puzzles, simple UI. A real pleasure
Excellent app, clean design, great features.

Good but tedious and cryptic. And no, that's not a good thing. The interface is somewhat confusing and it took me a few games to figure out the controls. Those first games were very frustrating. On the main page, where you pick your game, I still have not figured out what the small numbers in the corner of the game number mean. Classic case of the programmer knowing their program and assuming everyone else does as well. And I wish the hints came with explanations that made sense.
Mostly great app but for some reason it causes the home and back buttons to disappear from the bottom of my touchscreen.
Absolutley phenomenal app. Wouldn't change a thing. Great job Cracking the Cryptic!
It's a fine Sudoku app, but only 60 games for the price is a bit much.
Just spot the X-wing
Please add option to create my own sudoku
Love it! And love the channel!
Wonderful and challenging app, easy to use!

Great selection of sudokus, with good guidance and targeted hints, since I'm often struggling to identify the advanced techniques on my own. However, app is very power hungry so I can't use it out and about without flattening my battery
Great app, and more importantly, great sudoku.
Simon and Mark have some of the best puzzle content on the internet, and this app is no exception. Thank you for enriching my life with sudoku and cryptic crosswords. Cheers from Canada!
Amazing. Really well crafted Sudoku puzzles with amazing hints that actually teach you how to solve Sudoku.
No way to restore progress? Switched to a new phone. Looked like none of the levels are showing cleared.
Best sudoku app I've ever used

This is a great app from a great team. I've enjoyed the challenging hand crafted puzzles. The only thing really preventing this from being a 5* review is the lack of a true dark mode and the amount of battery it seems to be eating up when I play (maybe those are related). Other than that, I recommend people buy this. It's worth the money. Oh yeah...I would like a layout for landscape/tablets and a way to mark completed puzzles that were tough to replay later. Those aren't impacting my review.
Brilliant handmade Sudokus from the 'Cracking the Cryptic' team.
Great app
So much better than all the computer generated puzzles. Hot tip is to turn off all the error highlighting and row/column highlighting as frankly it just develops bad habits.

Very great Sudokus with the best hints I've ever seen. Instead of just giving you a number, it explains the logic of what to do next very clearly. This app along with their YouTube channel "Cracking the Cryptic" has helped me improve so much in these types of puzzles
It's got a really lovely interface and interesting puzzles! I mostly wish that you could input custom puzzles.
Best sudoku app on the market
Brilliant.
This is a good Sudoku app. Simple to use. No ads No fluff. Just games. :)
This app has given me hours of enjoyment

Love the handcrafted puzzles created for this app, thanks for the hard work Mark and Simon. My only criticism is that it is tedious to input numbers near the end of the puzzle. It would be a great quality of life addition to allow us to hold a number then place that number throughout the grid.
Brilliant App. Had to manually enable both corner and centre notation from the settings.

It's a good interface. Not great but good. The cost is too much for the 50 puzzles you get for this price IMO. There are many free and/or less $ sudoku apps that provide more puzzles. There is no "enter your own" puzzle capability. This too is a major drawback IMO.

The best thing about this app is the quality of the puzzles, although I would like to see more difficult puzzles. The interface could be better, the most annoying thing in my opinion is that the numbers are lined up in a row instead of like a numberpad. Because of this the numbers are too small and it takes more effort to press them regardless of size, because pressing the right position in a numberpad is easier to do without looking closely.
Very good puzzles. I can tell it's hand crafted. Great job. Probably not for beginners (watch their YouTube channel first!)

It's a good app, but my god why can I not have little numbers in both the middle and around the outside like in your YouTube channel? You learn one way watching on YouTube and buy the app only not to be allowed the same tools. When you select centred little number notation, it converts all outside numbers to the centre when you enter a new digit. A terrible way to do it.
It's very good. Best sudoku app I've used and the puzzles are handcrafted which makes the solutions much more satisfying.
Best Sudoku app I've used!
Great user interface
Great sudoku app. It's a huge bonus to be able to enter pencil notation in different positions, most apps don't support this. They are nicely designed puzzles too.
Great puzzles, really hard. Custom hints, really well, individually made puzzles.

Lovely app, beautiful puzzles, by far the best sudoku app in existence. Handcrafted puzzles made with thought and care about the users experience. An absolute delight to use. Absolutely worth the money, much cheaper than a sudoku book and it comes with the convenience of being on your phone. Would love to be able to make corner and central notation amd maybe an option for larger number buttons as it can be a little bit fiddly when trying to input a note and accidentally pressing the wrong number
Excellent puzzles that are difficult, but always possible. Best interface for sudoku, in fact I wish I could add puzzles from newspapers into the app to use the interface.

Almost the perfect sudoku app! I've knocked off two stars for the following: 1) There's no option to add an external puzzle. The controls are fantastic, some of the best out there & it's a shame you can't manually add (or even better, use the camera to add) a puzzle from somewhere else. Please add this feature for another star! 2) No support for dark mode or a dark option. Playing at night or in low light is a bit harsh on the eyes, so please can you add a dark/night colour option. Thanks!
Really lovely puzzles

I have a true appreciation for the creators of these puzzles. The puzzles are challenging and stunning. I learned several solving techniques I didn't know before. I originally rated the app as a 3 star. They had typos in a few hints, but they fixed the levels I mentioned. Great support, nothing more I could ask. Highly Recommend!

The puzzles are good and enjoyable so far, and the content produced by the YouTube channel is really great - it's helped me improve a lot. Improvements can and should be made though. The number buttons are very small, and they're way too low on the screen. If your phone has an onscreen menu bar, it will frequently get in the way - it would be easy enough to shift the puzzle board higher up, as there's plenty of space. Also, it would be good to have a more night mode style colour option.
Fantastic puzzles. Wonderful user interface. Number buttons could be a little bigger. I would also like to be able to enter my own puzzles just to use the interface to solve them.

Started doing these a few weeks after I didn't feel I was getting better at them on other apps. The first puzzle took me like 45 mins that time. Went back to it today having forgotten it and got through it in about 6minutes. I do watch the YouTube channel too so no doubt that is bringing me on, I'll never be a master but I'm getting better. Great app, thanks.
Excellent Sudoku app, allowing to mark cells with two kinds of small digits and several colors and automatic highlighting of matching numbers. Very responsive designer.

A lot of the hints are outright wrong. Puzze 13, hint #5 for example suggest a triplet in a square where one of the triplet numbers are not allowed. Please proof-read the hints. We have paid for this.

Hello Simon and Mark. New follower of your YouTube Channel and recently started on your app. Excellent work and fantastic puzzles. My only request would be for the digits entered to be a slightly more noticeable colour than the given digits. Other than that, fantastic work!
Great app, but needs more puzzles. And the hints are meant to teach you, but they assume you have a base knowledge. I like the YouTube videos associated with the creator, but the app needs attention.
Not recommended for tablet users. It refuses to use landscape orientation. Also it has no way to get out of that app on a phone. Skip this one.

Love the app so far. Everything I wanted in a sudoku app. Brilliant and intuitive UI, a wonderful notation system that makes using whatever method of notation you prefer a dream. Simon and Mark, you have out done yourselves!
Great sudokus that also teach you required techniques if you're not familiar with them yet. 5/5, would buy again!
Brilliant, really appreciate Cracking the Cryptic, this app is a gem, a pleasure, a truly enjoyable experience.
Super intuitive and useful to guide and reinforce learning. Only wish it was easy to exit out of the game once I'm done for the moment (exit button on the main menu?)

Solid app, best Sudoku app I've used. I'd recommend having larger numbers to press for input. The buttons are smaller than I'd like (and there's a lot of unused space nearer the top of the screen, perhaps the grid can be moved upward?). It makes for some fat finger moments. I need to turn off autocheck just to avoid unwanted "spoilers." Functionality is perfect for me though, highlights are very useful.

Excellent app with amazing selection of curated puzzles with tips that help me become a better Sudoku player. If you want to get better at Sudoku, this is definitely worth the money compared to all of the free apps that are out there. My one complaint is that the hints take up the full screen with giant text, so I can't look at the board while I'm reading the hint so I need to keep switching back and forth.

Brilliant app. The hints are really useful. They explain why a number is placed in a certain position so you can see just which bit of logic you totally missed. Like having a home sudoku tutor. Every type of notation and highlighting is there. Worth every penny.
The app won't just open at all! It just shows back screen all the time! What do I do?

Beautiful puzzles with well-explained hints - playing through was so satisfying! There is no other sudoku app like it, 1000% worth it . (just want to say I love your youtube channel, id never been into puzzles before and now I'm a big fan!)

Just bought it yesterday and so far happy with it. One small issue thought, the timer on Galaxy S10 is right under the front cameras and can't be seen. The same happens at every screen that has something at the top right corner. I see there are 40 games, what happens after they are all played?
Same layout and controls as the Sandwich Sudoku but does not keep track of completed numbers. Meh! The app could be better.
I love the two types of notes however I cant get any cells to highlight.
Got a refund. App is too awkward and slow to navigate, numbers are too small. There are much better free options
Superb app. Each puzzle well designed. Cannot praise enough!
This is a great Sudoku app. Truly a huge fan of this app.
Great app and wonderful puzzles. A real challenge and a lot of fun.
Been waiting on this to release. It does not disappoint.

Absolutely beautifully hand crafted sudoku puzzles that are easily worth the price. As you progress you need more solving skills UNTIL you get to the last one which took me four tries until I solved it. Now I can't wait until there's more for which I'd happily pay. Bravo gentlemen. If you can, is it possible to allow us to enter and save our own sudoku puzzles. That could be a separate charge which i would happily pay for. Again, congratulations gentlemen.
By far, the best sudoku app I've played. Well worth the purchase. If you appreciate hand-crafted puzzles you will not be disappointed.
Solid app. Superb content. Would recommend

Figuring out what all the icons do led to me deleting my progress twice. Numbers are way too small to press, there's lots of screen space that could be used for the number boxs but instead are jammed onto one small line at the bottom. Kind of enjoyed that there appeared to be no hint button, but instead it was just hidden inside an info button for reasons (?). I feel like you don't need the "what is suduko" stuff with a paid app + the difficulty to start is way to difficult for a beginner.
A most excellent sudoku app with some truly unique puzzles
Great App
The very best UI for sudoku!
Awesome app! Great puzzles and really useful GUI.
Fantastic hand set puzzles! You won't find this quality of Sudoku puzzles in any other app. Great interface and controls as well
Well worth the money, the amount of care put into this app is phenomenal. No bugs, no ads and no nags. Great puzzles and a wide range of difficulty.

Really great app with so much customisability within settings so I can set it up to how I like it. Was a bit worried with the default "single notation" and the 5's overlapping with the "centre notation". Problem solved being able to change it to "double notation". Would love a black/white theme in to preserve battery on an OLED and an option to play the YouTube puzzles even without hints etc. Perfect timing for release, my long haul flight entertainment for tomorrow is sorted :)

Great app by the greatest sudoku channel on YouTube. Only issue is the occasional soft lock after completing a puzzle. The screen starts to fade to the puzzle selection menu and then stops midway, causing me to have to restart the app.
Beautiful handcrafted sudoku puzzles. The UI is very well thought out.
Awesome set of puzzles and very nice app to work with.
Wonderful puzzles for pocket change!
Incredible Sudoku app with satisfying hand crafted puzzles.

This is such a good app if you enjoy sudoku. Most of the puzzles are pretty hard but they're a lot better than most of the auto-generated puzzles you'll find from other apps. The interface works great, is decently intuitive, and allows you to do a lot more extensive note-taking than some other apps.

This is the Sodoku app I've been waiting for. It's the only one that allows both corner and center notes for advanced marking. The puzzles it comes with are all hand created which means there are some methods needed to solve them you'd never see in the usual symmetrical computer generated ones. This also means there hints that pertain specifically to the puzzle you're working on. I've only done the first one so far and want to go back and try it again since I'm pretty sure there were some obvious things I missed that would have sped things up. I do wish one could enter puzzles manually as there are some really good ones out there. Perhaps this will be considered for a future update. With 5 new ones a month though, I suspect I'll have plenty to keep me busy for a good while. Finally, this app does allow itself to be moved to an SD card so kudos for that.

Very clean sudoku app with great controls. It's obvious that some serious consideration has been made for usability. The puzzles are challenging, but the quality of puzzles is probably the exact reason you're buying the app in the first place.
There really is a huge difference between a mass generated Sudoku and crafted Sudoku. A "quick test" became 60 minutes. Can't recall when last I enjoyed a logic puzzle this much.

I love how easy it is to markup this Sudoku app, they clearly put in a lot of time to help you clearly solve the way you prefer to do it. Some fun puzzles and they give you great hints on the hard ones to get you started and thinking without just telling you the answer.
Awesome Sudoku App.
I love the interface as I'm just getting back into the puzzles after finding your channel. I just wish there was a way to input user puzzles to use with your interface on Android.

I find myself struggling a bit with some of the early puzzles; having to diligently search for that one naked single or pair that I've missed to progress. Not sure if that's intended to force us to practice scanning or if I'm too thick to be lead through the solve. :) Definitely more satisfying to complete than computer generated puzzles.
As good as the hosts. The puzzles are damn hard though ahahaha
